-- Old Mutual's wealth arm buys UK's Quilter Cheviot
-- By Karolin Schaps
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 02:27AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 17 (Reuters) - Financial services group Old Mutual's <OML.L> wealth arm will acquire investment management firm Quilter Cheviot for 585 million pounds($940.97 million), the company said on Friday.

The takeover will give the joint entity 92 billion pounds of funds under management and is in line with Old Mutual's return on equity target of 12-15 percent.